= The Frankfurt Negotiations

# reference: Evans, Ellen L. “Adam Stegerwald and the Role of the Christian Trade Unions in the Weimar Republic.” The Catholic Historical Review 59, no. 4 (1974): 602–26.

The rise of both the Far-Right and the Far-Left has compelled even the Labour faction in our party to consider more negotiations with the Center and DDP in order to prevent their ascension to power - in local elections, at least. The Left have expressed their objections, arguing that our current cooperation levels with the bourgeioise are more than enough already.

As such, they have proposed meeting in Farnkfurt with Bruning and Stressman to develop, negotiate and implement several actions meant to keep Germany democracy alive.

We are expected to lead the conference, so naturally, to finance it too. 

- @yes_meet: Our republic needs salvation!
- @no_meet: It isn't worth it

